<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ ``Please don't pass any more
laws,'' wrote Bill Hobby, Texas' former lieutenant governor. Hobby
is in a position to know what is best for Texas. He is one of
Texas' most respected public servants. (Rowland Nethaway is senior
editor of the Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Eanes school district trustees
laid a large egg when they picked the supposedly members-only
Austin Country Club to interview their three finalists for
superintendent. If this place is exclusive, then I'm a Mongolian
sheepherder. Trust me. They'll let any jerk in at this club. I
know, because on Tuesday I managed to worm my way in for lunch at
the Austin Country Club. And I'm not a member. (Kelso, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
