<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The spotlight is on. . .
 &HT;    Staff reports
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Steven Soderbergh (director, ``Out of Sight'')
</P>
<P>
   ``sex, lies, &AMP; videotape'': This drama about lust and deception,
starring Andie MacDowell and James Spader, made history as the
first independent film to become a box office hit.
</P>
<P>
   ``Kafka'': Jeremy Irons stars in this surreal doodle of a movie,
paying homage to author Franz Kafka's world of bureaucratic menace.
</P>
<P>
   ``King of the Hill'': Underrated (and seen by few), this
powerful drama concerns a 12-year-old boy's struggle to survive the
Depression, with little help from his drifter dad.
</P>
