<P>
   UNDATED _ The misuse of antibiotics and the associated increase
in drug-resistant bacteria has been a hotly debated topic in the
medical community for 10 years, but the answer has always been to
develop newer, stronger antibiotics. Now, some doctors say, it's
time to find alternatives. (Accompanied by ANTIBIOTICS-TOP 10 and
ANTIBIOTICS-FYI BOX.) By CAROLYN POIROT. Story will move in ``l''
lifestyle category &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ANDERSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Some people think that our lives change like the
seasons: spring, summer, fall and winter. Others say that we go
through stages from infancy to infantile. I kind of like to think
of life as one long line with a point of origin here on Earth that
swerves and curves until it extends to areas that are ultimately
beyond our sight. By MONICA FRAZIER ANDERSON. Story will move in
``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
