<P>
   UNDATED _ Is it deja vu, or has time stood still for two weeks?
Here I am, back from a year-end vacation, and the headlines are
exactly the same as they were in mid-December 1998: presidential
impeachment, America vs. Iraq, the usual suspects gearing up for
the 2000 presidential election. By BILL THOMPSON. Story will move
in ``k'' commentary category &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LABBE-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Hark, the heralds are singing good news about
decreasing crime in America. The FBI reported last month that
serious crimes dropped 5 percent in the first half of 1998,
extending a six-year trend of improvement in the decline of
criminal activity. Using preliminary figures from police
departments nationwide, the FBI showed drops in all seven major
crime categories. The obvious question to follow such remarkable
news is: ``Why? What are we doing that is contributing to this
decline?'' By J.R. LABBE. Story will move in ``k'' commentary
category &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
