<P>
   The Atlanta Journal-Constitution is moving the following story
</P>
<P>
   MINDSPRING _ MindSpring Enterprises joined the ranks of the
giants of the Internet today when it announced the planned purchase
of the domestic consumer base of Netcom from ICG Communications.
MindSpring will pay $215 million in cash as well as $30 million in
MindSpring stock in a deal worth $245 million. (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
