<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP07-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Corn and ham team for cool, hot soup
 &HT;    By Marcia Langhenry
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ After she lost her only copy, Mary Beth Reed of
Lithonia (Ga.) requested a repeat of this spicy corn and ham soup
published 10 years ago. The recipe won Edith Shiver of Leary a trip
to the Bahamas back then in the Georgia Farm Bureau Souper Dairy
Recipe Contest in Macon (Ga.). Good hot or cold, this soup even
takes to calorie-cutting: Substitute 4 cups skim milk for the milk
and half-and-half.
</P>
<P>
   SOUP
</P>
<P>
   Corn 'n Ham Cream Soup
</P>
<P>
   Makes 8 servings
</P>
<P>
   Preparation time: 10 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Cooking time: 20 minutes
</P>
<P>
   1 small onion
</P>
<P>
   2 cups cream-style corn, fresh, frozen or canned
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons butter
</P>
<P>
   6 ounces lean cured ham, chopped finely
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon hot pepper sauce
</P>
<P>
   1 rib celery, chopped
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon white pepper
</P>
<P>
   2 cups milk
</P>
<P>
   2 cups half-and-half
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon dried parsley flakes
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons pimentos, chopped
</P>
<P>
   3 ounces cheddar cheese, shredded
</P>
<P>
   1 cup whipping cream, whipped
</P>
<P>
   Nutmeg for garnish, optional
</P>
<P>
   Fresh mint sprigs for garnish
</P>
<P>
   Put onion and corn in blender and puree.
</P>
<P>
   In a 2-quart saucepan melt butter on medium-low heat. Add
chopped ham and cook 5 minutes, stirring. Add pureed corn mixture,
salt, hot pepper sauce, celery, white pepper and 1/2 cup milk. Cook
10 minutes on medium heat, stirring to mix well.
</P>
<P>
   Add 1 1/2 cups milk, half-and-half and parsley flakes. Cover;
heat on medium-low to simmering, stirring often. Remove from heat.
</P>
<P>
   Stir in pimentos and grated cheddar cheese. Mix well. Keep hot
until ready to serve if hot soup is desired. If cold soup is
desired, cool and chill in refrigerator. Serve chilled soup in a
small cup as an appetizer.
</P>
<P>
   When serving soup, hot or cold, place a mound of whipped cream
on top of each serving in soup bowl or cup. Garnish with a dash of
nutmeg and a sprig of mint.
</P>
<P>
   Per serving (without garnishes): 327 calories, 15 grams protein,
6 grams fat (percent calories from fat, 64), 19 grams
carbohydrates, 83 milligrams cholesterol, 184 milligrams sodium, 1
gram fiber.
</P>
<P>
   Requests
</P>
<P>
   Where to write
</P>
<P>
   Recipes or requests for recipes for this column should be sent
to Recipe Swap, Food Department, The Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302. Include a daytime telephone
number. E-mail: mlanghenry(at)ajc.com
</P>
<P>
   _ Marcia Langhenry is a staff writer for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
