<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   UN-IRAQ (New York) _ Impartiality of the UN is at stake as
questions flow about improper UN-US connections in maintaining
surveillance of Iraqi weapons. By Colum Lynch. 1300 words.
</P>
<P>
   PRINCE-ENGAGED (London) _ Prince Edward, Queen Elizabeth's
youngest son, and his longtime girlfriend, Sophie Rhys-Jones, are
getting married. By Kevin Cullen. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; IMPEACHMENT (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-TRIAL (Washington) _ House Republicans say they'll push
to compel testimony by the principals in the Clinton impeachment
trial in the Senate. By Bob Hohler and Ann Scales. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-ANALYSIS (Washington) _ The deeper Congress and the
White House wade into a historic impeachment trial, the deeper the
differences between the tragedies of Andrew Johnson and Bill
Clinton appear. By David M. Shribman. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CONGRESS-ISSUES (Washington) _ The 106th Congress gets under way
amid impeachment conflicts and other thorny issues. By Michael
Kranish. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   DOOMSDAY-FLARES (Undated) _ Astronomers say stars similar to the
sun have shot explosive flares into space, raising a new doomsday
scenario: A sun flare wipes out the earth's ozone layer in an hour,
ending the food chain and causing mass starvation. By David L.
Chandler. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-CIVIL (Boston) _ ``A Civil Action'' premieres amid the
usual Hollywood hoopla -- only this time in Boston. By Joseph P.
Kahn. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   CIVIL-FAMILIES (Boston) _ The families, the real stars of ``A
Civil Action,'' give the movie mixed reviews. For most, the making
of the movie, and now its debut, have renewed their sorrow and
rage. By Doreen Iudica. 700 words. (a coding)
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   CIVIL-LAWYER (Boston) _ The ``bad guys'' in ``A Civil Action''
-- the lawyers defending the alleged toxic waste dumpers -- have
one complaint: The movie ignores the fact that they actually won
the case. By Judy Rakowsky. 500 words. (a coding)
</P>
