husband, Bill, were at the breaking point with their 1940s fishing
boat, the S.S. Michigan. Every time they took the boat out,
something happened. It has sunk nine times, its hull has been stove
in and it has caught fire. Enter the Rev. Joe Warren of Newport
Beach, an ordained minister who, with his Brothers of the Riverboat
Angela Louise, performs boat exorcisms. 
By Jeremy Bagott. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
OUT-BAN (San Diego) _ For the first time Wednesday, the state Fish
and Game Commission was to hear an action item on a proposal to ban
commercial harvesting and sport-fishing along no less than 20
percent of the coastline of the six northernmost Channel Islands.
The implications could pave the way to a conclusion to the often
volatile proposal that commercail anglers say will limit their
livelihoods and evokes the ire of sportsmen alike. 
By Brett Pauly. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
