</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Here are some ideas on keeping it cool in the office
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Though some like it hot, you might want it cold _ or at least a
bit cooler. If you belong in this camp, try these items:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  COOL DRINKS. When you're super-thirsty, resort to the Pump Pot
(right) with a glass thermal liner ($12.97). Fill the 2.6-quart
container with your favorite cold beverage, then sip away. At
Wal-Mart.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  FAN-TASTIC. Look and feel cool with Holmes' Euro Style desk
fan ($9.99). The 10-by-10-inch electric box fan with two speeds
fits neatly on a desktop and doesn't disturb co-workers.
</P>
<P>
   Or, for a flash of air, try Holmes' pocket cooler fan ($4.99).
This battery-operated fan fits neatly into the palm of your hand.
Both fans are available online at http://www
</P>
<P>
   .kmart.com. Starting in February, the seasonal items will also
be available in Kmart stores, according to Ernie Morse, manager at
the Kennesaw Kmart.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  WEARABLE AIR CONDITIONER. Invest in your own Personal Cooling
System (below) from the Sharper Image. The lightweight aluminum
collar fits around the neck. You simply fill its two chambers with
a few ounces of water, rest it on your neck and switch it on. A
quiet, tiny fan moves air across the water, cooling the area around
you up to 20 degrees. The flexible sides hold the cooling plate
against your neck _ and you feel cool all over. It weighs 16 ounces
filled. ($49). To order:
</P>
<P>
   1-800-344-4444.
</P>
