slump in prices for hogs doesn't seem to affect what shoppers pay
for pork here - at Gepperth's Meat Market in Chicago - or
elsewhere. As a result, allegations of price-gouging are being
leveled against the meatpackers who turn hogs into pork products,
and to a lesser extent against the giant supermarket
chainsretailers that sell them. (Steve Kagan/New York Times Photo)
