Norah Pierson's home, encased in a rocky shell some 20 miles
southeast of Santa Fe, is known locally as the Flintstone house. It
may be the only house in America whose exterior was architecturally
inspired by a 50-foot-long, 14-foot-high polyurethane brontosaurus.
(Cary Herz/New York Times Photo)
