<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SHE DOESN'T NEED NO STINKING RESOLUTIONS
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; President Clinton &LR; 's participation at the Renaissance weekend
was strictly drop-in, reports the Chicago Tribune, limited to
hitting some golf balls and making a few remarks on New Year's Eve.
</P>
<P>
   When someone asked the first lady if she had any New Year's
resolutions, she said, ``I was on the cover of Vogue magazine. I
don't need any resolutions.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LOVE AND MARRIAGE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   In an adoring Harper's Bazaar interview with the adorable
 &UR; John &LR;   &UR; Travolta  &LR; and  &UR; Kelly Preston &LR; , Travolta recalls the first
time he met Preston. She was married.
</P>
<P>
   ``I said, `How do you like being married?' and she said, `I love
it,' and I loved that answer, because even though that marriage
didn't work out, she loved the idea of being married, and that was
important to me.''
</P>
<P>
   After Preston's divorce, she became engaged to  &UR; Charlie &LR; 
 &UR; Sheen &LR; . ``I knew that wouldn't work out,'' said the romantic
Travolta.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; GREEN WITH ENVY &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Larry Gelbart &LR;  told the AARP Bulletin that he thought he was
doing well with crossword puzzles ``because I was doing them in
pen. Then I learned  &UR; Stephen Sondheim &LR;  was doing them in his
head.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Duking it out in the sky: A billboard atop the building at
Post and Powell in San Francisco, ``Wrap up your holiday shopping
at Borders,'' is intended to dominate the northwest corner of Union
Square. But if you're looking west up Post Street, observes
 &UR; Ken Maley &LR; , the dominating billboard is strategically placed on the
side of 450 Post, a much taller building: ``Can't find your book or
CD? Amazon.com.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Barbra Streisand &LR;  has signed for ``an eight-figure amount,''
says the New York Post, to perform at the MGM Grand in Las Vegas on
New Year's Eve 1999.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Melanie Griffith &LR;  reveals in the latest W that ``It was
really gritty. And violent,'' being directed by  &UR; Larry Clark  &LR; in
``Another Day in Paradise,'' a movie about a junkie crime couple.
``One of the things that helped me was that Larry really is a
heroin addict,'' Griffith said. The director has since checked into
a rehab clinic.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHAT IT TAKES TO MAKE FINE ART &LR;
</P>
<P>
   In a survey reported in the latest edition of the artists
newsletter studioNOTES, artists were asked about the effect of
mind-altering practices (meditation, trance, music or the like) or
substances (alcohol, drugs, tobacco, caffeine or the like) on the
creative process.
</P>
<P>
   Respondents wrote about coffee and cigarettes, Zen meditation,
vodka, chocolate, psychedelics and in-depth Jungian analysis. One
of the most intriguing anecdotes came from a woman who had
submitted a batch of drawings to her art teacher at the end of a
course.
</P>
<P>
   She was the best draftsman in the class, she wrote, and had sold
some of her work to other students.
</P>
<P>
   The teacher looked at the work and asked, ``How much marijuana
do you smoke?''
</P>
<P>
   ``I said a lot. He said he could tell. I was flabbergasted. He
pointed out that there was little contrast in much of my work _ it
was all a bit `mushy.' ... That was typical of dopers, he said.
They get very inspired and involved in detail, &LR;  but lose the
contrast and value. This is also how they see the world.''
</P>
<P>
   She thought about it for a few days, she writes, and ``never
took another drug.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not arrogant. I'm not arrogant at all, as a matter of
fact. I think I have a lot of humility, but I will not acknowledge
_ nor do I think I should have to _ power structures that have been
patriarchally put in place by people other than myself.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Courtney Love in Allure magazine.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
